Pascale de Boysson https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pascale_de_Boysson 0 Pascale de Boysson (16 April 1922–9 August 2002) was a French film, television and stage actress who also adapted and translated plays for the French stage. She was a two-time winner of the Molière Award, winning it in 1988 and posthumously in 2003.
